Uses of Package
siccom.sim

  • Packages that use siccom.sim 
    Package Description
    siccom.sim  
  • Classes in siccom.sim used by siccom.sim 
    Class and Description
    BranchingGroup
    This class defines the main parameters for a branching coral species For parameter description of individual colonies see BranchingCoral For parameter which are important for all coral groups see CoralGroup
    CoralGroup
    Defines the parameters for a CoralGroup which then can be used to instantiate the coral individuals.
    MassiveGroup
    This class defines the main parameters for a massive coral species For parameter description of individual colonies see MassiveCoral For parameter which are important for all coral groups see CoralGroup
    OutputWriter
    Writes the output files to the output folder
    ParameterFile
    This class takes a File or InputStreamReader object as a reference and opens and read the existing parameter file: It reads all lines and creates a ParmEntry object for every to store the information. It stores the read values by the name of the entry.
    Siccom 
    Temperature
    This class handles the temperature data The different years of the data set are accessed randomly and the one extreme year (1998) is accessed when the bleaching interval is reached
